    • Method Detail

      • getId

        String getId()
        The unique identifier of the function that is used for registration and identification of the aggregation method. The id is an internal used variable that is not displayed to the user.
        Returns:
        the unique id of this function

      • getLabel

        String getLabel()
        Returns:
        the label that is displayed to the user

      • isCompatible

        boolean isCompatible(DataType type)
        Parameters:
        type - the DataType check for compatibility
        Returns:
        true if the aggregation method is compatible

      • getDescription

        String getDescription()
        Returns:
        the description for this function

      • hasOptionalSettings

        boolean hasOptionalSettings()
        This method indicates if the operator requires additional settings. If that is the case the operator should return true. It must also override the corresponding methods (#getSettingsPanel(DataTableSpec), #validateSettings(NodeSettingsRO), #loadValidatedSettings(NodeSettingsRO), #saveSettingsTo(NodeSettingsWO) and #resetSettings()).
        Returns:
        true if the operator requires additional settings
        See Also:
        getSettingsPanel(), validateSettings(NodeSettingsRO), loadValidatedSettings(NodeSettingsRO), loadSettingsFrom(NodeSettingsRO, DataTableSpec), saveSettingsTo(NodeSettingsWO)

      • getSettingsPanel

        Component getSettingsPanel()
        Returns the optional Component that allows the user to adjust all DBAggregationFunction specific settings. Methods that do need additional settings must override this method in order to return their settings panel.
        Returns:
        the Component that contains all necessary settings

      • loadValidatedSettings

        void loadValidatedSettings(NodeSettingsRO settings)
                    throws InvalidSettingsException
        This method is called in the NodeModel to load the settings that have been saved (saveSettingsTo(NodeSettingsWO)) by the DBAggregationFunction used in the in the additional settings panel (getSettingsPanel()) into the DBAggregationFunction that is actually used in the NodeModel. Each operator gets its own NodeSettingsRO object to ensure the uniqueness of the settings keys.
        Parameters:
        settings - NodeSettingsRO that contains the optional settings
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - if a property is not available

      • loadSettingsFrom

        void loadSettingsFrom(NodeSettingsRO settings,
                      DataTableSpec spec)
               throws NotConfigurableException
        This method is called prior the getSettingsPanel() method is called and the dialog is opened. This method should be used to load all settings form the provided settings object and to adjust the corresponding dialog components accordingly. Each operator gets its own NodeSettingsRO object to ensure the uniqueness of the settings keys.
        Parameters:
        settings - NodeSettingsRO that contains the optional settings
        spec - the DataTableSpec of the input table
        Throws:
        NotConfigurableException - if the dialog cannot be opened because of invalid settings or if any preconditions are not fulfilled, e.g. no nominal column in input table, etc.

      • saveSettingsTo

        void saveSettingsTo(NodeSettingsWO settings)
        This method is called from the NodeDialog and NodeModel in order to save the additional settings. It is also called prior the getSettingsPanel() method in order to save the current settings. The saved settings are used to initialize the settings panel by calling loadSettingsFrom(NodeSettingsRO, DataTableSpec) prior calling getSettingsPanel() and to restore the previous (default) setting by calling the loadValidatedSettings(NodeSettingsRO) when the user closes the dialog in any other way then by clicking on the OK button! Each operator gets its own NodeSettingsRO object to ensure the uniqueness of the settings keys.
        Parameters:
        settings - the NodeSettingsWO to save the optional settings

      • validateSettings

        void validateSettings(NodeSettingsRO settings)
               throws InvalidSettingsException
        This method is called from the NodeDialog when the user closes the additional settings dialog by clicking on the OK button. It is also called from the NodeModel prior the settings are loaded calling the loadValidatedSettings(NodeSettingsRO). Each operator gets its own NodeSettingsRO object to ensure the uniqueness of the settings keys. This function has been replaced by the validate() method.
        Parameters:
        settings - the NodeSettingsRO that contains the optional settings to validate
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - if the settings are invalid
        See Also:
        validate()

      • validate

        void validate()
       throws InvalidSettingsException
        Validates the internal state (e.g. settings) of the function. This method is typically called in the node dialog in order to validate the settings of each AggregationFunction before saving it.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - if the internal state is invalid

      • configure

        void configure(DataTableSpec spec)
        throws InvalidSettingsException
        This method is called from NodeModel in the configure() in order to let the operator configure and to check that the aggregation operator can work with the available input table.
        Parameters:
        spec - the DataTableSpec of the input table
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - if the settings are invalid
        See Also:
        loadValidatedSettings(NodeSettingsRO)
